parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt system can lead to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: Seat belts latch and tracks are broken
seat belts slide back and forth
plastic covering on seat belt buckle coming off
seat belt buckle coming unattached during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to not properly restrain the occupant, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Seat belt retractor fails to retract

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to not properly restrain the occupant, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: plastic covering on seat belt buckle coming off
seat belt buckle coming unattached during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Acceleration and Unintended Vehicle Movement
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration and unintended vehicle movement can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as well as damage to property and other vehicles.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly and uncontrollably
often when shifting gears or with the foot on the brake
resulting in loss of vehicle control

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Uncontrolled engine acceleration can lead to accidents, especially when driving uphill or in reverse, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: especially when in reverse or on steep inclines
sudden acceleration from a stop position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded, especially when approaching a stop sign or applying the accelerator pedal.
symptoms: difficulty accelerating from a stop position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the water pump can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage, stalling, or failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Inadequate oil circulation can cause engine damage, leading to premature wear, overheating, or failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil not circulating to the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded, and may result in costly repairs or replacement.
Rusting of the engine cradle can lead to structural weakness, potentially causing the engine to fall out of the vehicle, resulting in loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion visible on the engine cradle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Door hinge failure can cause the door to separate from the vehicle while in motion, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: door difficult to open or close

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of bolts or mounts can cause the body to separate from the frame, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
